  "local_port": 41648,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I create hotspot for windows 10?",
  "response": "Creating a Wi-Fi hotspot using a Windows 10 computer is quite straightforward. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n### Option 1: Using Windows Settings\n\n1. **Open Settings**: Click on the Start menu and select \"Settings\" (the gear icon).\n\n2. **Go to Network & Internet**:\n   - Click on \"Network & Internet.\"\n   - Select \"Mobile hotspot\" from the left-side menu.\n\n3. **Configure Your Hotspot**:\n   - In the \"Mobile hotspot\" settings, toggle the switch to \"On.\"\n   - Select either \"Wi-Fi\" or \"Ethernet\" (which ever your PC is connected to) from the \"Share my Internet connection from\" dropdown menu.\n   - Under \"Network name\" and \"Network password,\" you will see the default values. You can change these if you want to create a different network name and password for your hotspot.\n\n4. **Allow Other Devices to Connect**:\n   - Make sure the option \"Share my Internet connection with other devices\" is turned on.\n\n### Option 2: Using Command Prompt\n\n1. **Open Command Prompt**:\n   - Press `Windows + X` and select \"Command Prompt (Admin)\" or \"Windows PowerShell (Admin)\" from the menu.\n   \n2. **Set Up the Hotspot**:\n   - Type the following command and press Enter:\n     ```shell\n     netsh wlan set hostednetwork mode=allow ssid=Your_SSID key=Your_Password\n     ```\n   - Replace `Your_SSID` with the desired network name and `Your_Password` with a password you want to set for the hotspot.\n\n3. **Start the Hotspot**:\n   - Type the following command and press Enter:\n     ```shell\n     netsh wlan start hostednetwork\n     ```\n\n### Option 3: Using Third-Party Software\n\nThere are several third-party applications that can simplify the process of creating a hotspot on Windows 10. Some popular ones include:\n- **Connectify Hotspot**\n- **MyPublicWiFi**\n- **Virtual Router Plus**\n\nDownload and install one of these programs, and follow their instructions to create a Wi-Fi hotspot.\n\n### Troubleshooting\n\n- **Ensure Wi-Fi is Enabled**: Sometimes the mobile hotspot option might be grayed out if your Wi-Fi adapter is off. Ensure your Wi-Fi adapter is enabled.\n- **Update Network Drivers**: Make sure your network drivers are up-to-date to avoid any compatibility issues.\n- **Check Hardware Compatibility**: Not all network adapters support hotspot functionality. You can check adapter support by entering:\n  ```shell\n  netsh wlan show drivers\n  ```\n  Look for \"Hosted network supported\" line; it should say \"Yes.\"\n\nBy following these steps, you can set up a Wi-Fi hotspot on your Windows 10 computer to share your internet connection with other devices.",
